$PROBLEM    2 compartment fitting
$INPUT       ID TIME AMT DV WTKG GENDER AGE RATE
$DATA      C:\Workspace\Example2/datalarge.csv IGNORE=@

$SUBROUTINE ADVAN4 ;; advan4 ;; ADVAN2, ADVAN4, ADVAN12
$PK      
  CWTKGONE = WTKG/70  ;; CENTERED ON ONE
  CWTKGZERO = WTKG-70  ;; CENTERED ON ZERO
  CAGE = AGE/40 
  TVV2=THETA(2) *CWTKGONE**THETA(7) ;; optional covariates effects of WT and Gender
  V2=TVV2*EXP(ETA(2)) 
  TVCL= THETA(1)    ;; optional covariates effects of WT and AGE
  CL=TVCL*EXP(ETA(1)) 
  K=CL/V2 
  K23=THETA(4)*CWTKGONE**THETA(6)
  K32=THETA(5)*CWTKGONE**THETA(6)         ;; for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  D1=THETA(8)  ; infusion only         ;; include D1 and lag, with diag or block OMEGA

  TVKA=THETA(3) 
  KA=TVKA  *EXP(ETA(3))   
  S2 	= V2/1000 
$ERROR     
  REP = IREP      
  IPRED =F  
  IOBS = F +EPS(1)
  Y=IOBS
$THETA  ;; must be one THETA per line.
  (0.001,100)	; THETA(1) CL UNITS =  L/HR
  (0.001,500) 	; THETA(2) V  UNITS = L
  (0.001,2) 	; THETA(3) KA UNITS = 1/HR  

  (0.001,0.02)	 ;; THETA(4) K23
  (0.001,0.3) 	 ;; THETA(5) K32
  (0,0.1) 	; THETA(6) K23~WT 	 ;; init for K23~WT   ;; are initial estimates for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of weight needed?
  (-4,0.1,4) 	; THETA(7) POWER volume ~SEX    ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of gender needed?


  (0.01,0.2) 		;; THETA(8)
$OMEGA   ;; must be one ETA/line
  0.2  		; ETA(1) CLEARANCE
$OMEGA 
  0.2 	; ETA(2) VOLUME
  ;; optional $OMEGA blocks
  ;; optional initial estimates for ETA on KA
$OMEGA ;; 2nd??OMEGA block 
  0.1		; ETA(3) ETA ON KA

  ;; optional initial estimates for ETA on D1 and ALAG1
$OMEGA ;; 3rd??OMEGA block 
  0.1 		;; ETA(4) ETA ON D1
$SIGMA   

  3000 	; EPS(1) additive error   ;; additive or proportional or combined
$EST METHOD=COND INTER MAX = 9999 MSFO=MSF1 
$COV UNCOND PRINT=E

;; Phenotype 
;; OrderedDict([('ADVAN', 1), ('K23~WT', 1), ('KAETA', 1), ('V2~WT', 0), ('V2~GENDER', 1), ('CL~WT', 0), ('CL~AGE', 0), ('ETAD1LAG', 2), ('D1LAG', 1), ('RESERR', 1)])

  V2=TVV2*EXP(ETA(2))

  CL=TVCL*EXP(ETA(1))

  ALAG1=THETA(8)*EXP(ETA(4))

$INPUT       ID TIME AMT DV WTKG GENDER AGE RATE
$DATA      C:\Workspace\Example2/datalarge.csv IGNORE=@

$SUBROUTINE ADVAN4 ;; advan4 ;; ADVAN2, ADVAN4, ADVAN12
$PK      
  CWTKGONE = WTKG/70  ;; CENTERED ON ONE
  CWTKGZERO = WTKG-70  ;; CENTERED ON ZERO
  CAGE = AGE/40 
  TVV2=THETA(2)  ;; optional covariates effects of WT and Gender
  V2=TVV2*EXP(ETA(2)) 
  TVCL= THETA(1) *EXP(CWTKGZERO*THETA(6))  *CAGE**THETA(7) ;; optional covariates effects of WT and AGE
  CL=TVCL*EXP(ETA(1)) 
  K=CL/V2 
  K23=THETA(4)
  K32=THETA(5)         ;; for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  D1=THETA(8)  ; infusion only         ;; include D1 and lag, with diag or block OMEGA

  TVKA=THETA(3) 
  KA=TVKA  *EXP(ETA(3))   
  S2 	= V2/1000 
$ERROR     
  REP = IREP      
  IPRED =F  
  IOBS = F *EXP(EPS(1))+EPS(2)
  Y=IOBS
$THETA  ;; must be one THETA per line.
  (0.001,100)	; THETA(1) CL UNITS =  L/HR
  (0.001,500) 	; THETA(2) V  UNITS = L
  (0.001,2) 	; THETA(3) KA UNITS = 1/HR  

  (0.001,0.02)	 ;; THETA(4) K23
  (0.001,0.3) 	 ;; THETA(5) K32
  ;; init for K23~WT   ;; are initial estimates for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of weight needed?
  ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of gender needed?
  (-1,0.01,4) 	; THETA(6) EXPONENTIAL clearance~WT  
  (-4,-0.2,4) 	; THETA(7) POWER clearance~AGE  
  (0.01,0.2) 		;; THETA(8)
$OMEGA   ;; must be one ETA/line
  0.2  		; ETA(1) CLEARANCE
$OMEGA 
  0.2 	; ETA(2) VOLUME
  ;; optional $OMEGA blocks
  ;; optional initial estimates for ETA on KA
$OMEGA ;; 2nd??OMEGA block 
  0.1		; ETA(3) ETA ON KA

  ;; optional initial estimates for ETA on D1 and ALAG1
$OMEGA ;; 3rd??OMEGA block 
  0.1 		;; ETA(4) ETA ON D1
$SIGMA   

  0.3 	; EPS(1) proportional error
  0.3 	; EPS(2) additive error   ;; additive or proportional or combined
$EST METHOD=COND INTER MAX = 9999 MSFO=MSF1 
$COV UNCOND PRINT=E

;; Phenotype 
;; OrderedDict([('ADVAN', 1), ('K23~WT', 0), ('KAETA', 1), ('V2~WT', 0), ('V2~GENDER', 0), ('CL~WT', 2), ('CL~AGE', 1), ('ETAD1LAG', 2), ('D1LAG', 1), ('RESERR', 0)])
;; Genotype 
;; [1, 0, 1, 0, 0, 2, 1, 2, 1, 0]
;; Num non-influential tokens = 0

$PROBLEM    2 compartment fitting
$INPUT       ID TIME AMT DV WTKG GENDER AGE RATE
$DATA      C:\Workspace\Example2/datalarge.csv IGNORE=@

$SUBROUTINE ADVAN4 ;; advan4 ;; ADVAN2, ADVAN4, ADVAN12
$PK      
  CWTKGONE = WTKG/70  ;; CENTERED ON ONE
  CWTKGZERO = WTKG-70  ;; CENTERED ON ZERO
  CAGE = AGE/40 
  TVV2=THETA(2)*EXP(CWTKGZERO*THETA(6))  ;; optional covariates effects of WT and Gender
  V2=TVV2*EXP(ETA(2)) 
  TVCL= THETA(1)   *CAGE**THETA(7) ;; optional covariates effects of WT and AGE
  CL=TVCL*EXP(ETA(1)) 
  K=CL/V2 
  K23=THETA(4)
  K32=THETA(5)         ;; for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  ALAG1=THETA(9)*EXP(ETA(3))
  D1=THETA(8)*EXP(ETA(4))         ;; include D1 and lag, with diag or block OMEGA

  TVKA=THETA(3) 
  KA=TVKA    
  S2 	= V2/1000 
$ERROR     
  REP = IREP      
  IPRED =F  
  IOBS = F +EPS(1)
  Y=IOBS
$THETA  ;; must be one THETA per line.
  (0.001,100)	; THETA(1) CL UNITS =  L/HR
  (0.001,500) 	; THETA(2) V  UNITS = L
  (0.001,2) 	; THETA(3) KA UNITS = 1/HR  

  (0.001,0.02)	 ;; THETA(4) K23
  (0.001,0.3) 	 ;; THETA(5) K32
  ;; init for K23~WT   ;; are initial estimates for K23,K32,K24,K42 needed?
  (-1,0.01,2) 	; THETA(6) EXPONENTIAL volume ~WT    ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of weight needed?
  ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of gender needed?

  (-4,-0.2,4) 	; THETA(7) POWER clearance~AGE  
  (0.001,0.1,1) 		;; THETA on D1
  (0.001,0.1,1) ;; THETA on ALAG
$OMEGA   ;; must be one ETA/line
  0.2  		; ETA(1) CLEARANCE
$OMEGA

  ;; optional $OMEGA blocks
  ;; optional initial estimates for ETA on KA

$OMEGA  ;; diagonal OMEGA

  0.1 		;; ETA(4) ETA ON D1
$SIGMA   

  3000 	; EPS(1) additive error   ;; additive or proportional or combined
$EST METHOD=COND INTER MAX = 9999 MSFO=MSF1 
$COV UNCOND PRINT=E

  CAGE = AGE/40

  CL=TVCL*EXP(ETA(1))

  (0.001,500) 	; THETA(2) V  UNITS = L
  (0.001,2) 	; THETA(3) KA UNITS = 1/HR  

  (0.001,0.1) 	;; THETA(4) k23
  (0.001,0.1) 	;; THETA(5) k32
  (0.001,0.1) 	;; THETA(6) k24
  (0.001,0.1) 	;; THETA(7) k42

  (-4,0.1,4) 	; THETA(8) POWER volume ~SEX    ;;; is initial estimate for Volume a function of gender needed?
  (-1,0.01,4) 	; THETA(9) EXPONENTIAL clearance~WT  
  (-4,-0.2,4) 	; THETA(10) POWER clearance~AGE  
  (0.001,0.1,1) 		;; THETA on D1
  (0.001,0.1,1) ;; THETA on ALAG

$SIGMA   

  3000 	; EPS(1) additive error   ;; additive or proportional or combined
$EST METHOD=COND INTER MAX = 9999 MSFO=MSF1
